1
00:00:07,958 --> 00:00:09,250
[clattering, sizzling]

2
00:00:11,458 --> 00:00:13,625
[DERRIDA]
Wait! It's me! It's Derrida!

3
00:00:13,708 --> 00:00:15,666
Yeah, right.

4
00:00:15,750 --> 00:00:17,125
That can't be true.

5
00:00:17,208 --> 00:00:18,333
No, Derrida is...

6
00:00:18,416 --> 00:00:20,000
Listen to me. Where's Mage?

7
00:00:20,083 --> 00:00:21,541
Is she somewhere safe?

8
00:00:21,625 --> 00:00:22,916
Just tell me, please!

9
00:00:24,833 --> 00:00:26,375
I'm sorry.

10
00:00:27,416 --> 00:00:29,041
[YURI]
Mage is dead.

11
00:02:01,875 --> 00:02:03,833
That just can't be.

12
00:02:03,916 --> 00:02:06,083
[breeze blowing]

13
00:02:06,166 --> 00:02:07,625
Mage is dead?

14
00:02:07,708 --> 00:02:08,958
♪

15
00:02:09,041 --> 00:02:10,583
Come with me.

16
00:02:16,458 --> 00:02:17,500
Hmm?

17
00:02:19,375 --> 00:02:21,541
[grunting]

18
00:02:23,291 --> 00:02:25,416
[DERRIDA]
I thought this was a park.

19
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:28,375
[YURI]
It was, but that was years ago.

20
00:02:37,541 --> 00:02:39,125
[YURI]
Take a look.

21
00:02:39,208 --> 00:02:42,250
♪

22
00:02:43,291 --> 00:02:45,625
But that's... impossible.

23
00:02:49,375 --> 00:02:50,958
[DERRIDA]
Mage...

24
00:02:51,916 --> 00:02:53,833
I'm sorry, but it's true.

25
00:02:53,916 --> 00:02:56,375
She's buried right here.

26
00:02:58,875 --> 00:02:59,833
[DERRIDA]
No way.

27
00:03:01,458 --> 00:03:04,041
Tell me. What...

28
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,333
What killed her?

29
00:03:06,416 --> 00:03:08,333
How could this have
happened to her?

30
00:03:08,416 --> 00:03:10,416
[YURI]
What do you think?

31
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:12,416
It was the war, of course.

32
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:14,541
And it wasn't just her.

33
00:03:14,625 --> 00:03:17,583
Do you know how many
casualties there've been?

34
00:03:17,666 --> 00:03:19,833
[DERRIDA]
The war.

35
00:03:19,916 --> 00:03:22,500
I've been gone for 10 years,

36
00:03:23,458 --> 00:03:25,500
and this is what I wake up to?

37
00:03:25,583 --> 00:03:28,000
[YURI]
Seriously, who are you?

38
00:03:28,083 --> 00:03:29,291
[DERRIDA]
Hmm?

39
00:03:29,375 --> 00:03:30,416
[gasp]

40
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:32,416
I'm Derrida! Derrida Yvain!

41
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:35,166
I'm a friend of Mage's father,
Nathan, don't you remember?

42
00:03:35,250 --> 00:03:37,000
You have to remember me!

43
00:03:37,083 --> 00:03:38,666
You were Mage's friend,
you love cameras and--

44
00:03:38,750 --> 00:03:40,541
You're a liar! Derrida's dead!

45
00:03:40,625 --> 00:03:42,625
That man killed Nathan Bilstein,

46
00:03:42,708 --> 00:03:44,333
-And then he killed himsel--
-No, you're wrong!

47
00:03:44,416 --> 00:03:46,583
That's not true, I was framed!

48
00:03:46,666 --> 00:03:49,083
By that snake,
Andrei, at Rebuild.

49
00:03:49,166 --> 00:03:50,875
♪

50
00:03:50,958 --> 00:03:53,208
[wind blowing]

51
00:03:54,416 --> 00:03:56,875
[jewels clinking]

52
00:04:06,958 --> 00:04:09,708
[DONNA] Souls of the dead
deserve respect.

53
00:04:11,291 --> 00:04:14,166
Didn't anyone ever teach you
that when you visit a grave,

54
00:04:14,250 --> 00:04:16,500
you're supposed
to bring flowers?

55
00:04:16,583 --> 00:04:18,083
[YURI]
Huh?

56
00:04:19,833 --> 00:04:21,041
Who are...?

57
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:22,791
-[breeze]
-[grunt]

58
00:04:22,875 --> 00:04:25,708
♪

59
00:04:26,666 --> 00:04:28,875
[energy humming]

60
00:04:29,833 --> 00:04:31,333
[chuckle]

61
00:04:31,416 --> 00:04:32,500
[blast]

62
00:04:32,583 --> 00:04:33,875
[VIDAUX]
Derrida! Back away from her!

63
00:04:33,958 --> 00:04:34,875
[gunfire]

64
00:04:37,208 --> 00:04:38,125
[cloak whipping]

65
00:04:39,291 --> 00:04:40,166
[slice]

66
00:04:41,125 --> 00:04:42,750
-Get going!
-[slice]

67
00:04:42,833 --> 00:04:44,166
Hurry to Graham, now!

68
00:04:44,250 --> 00:04:45,041
[yelp]

69
00:04:45,125 --> 00:04:46,125
Not so fast.

70
00:04:46,208 --> 00:04:47,083
[panting]

71
00:04:48,958 --> 00:04:50,375
[panting]

72
00:04:50,458 --> 00:04:51,916
[grunting]

73
00:04:52,875 --> 00:04:53,875
-[grunt]
-[gasp]

74
00:04:53,958 --> 00:04:54,958
[VIDAUX grunts]

75
00:04:55,916 --> 00:04:56,958
How dare you.

76
00:04:57,041 --> 00:04:58,416
I can't have you
hurting my client.

77
00:04:58,500 --> 00:05:00,333
-[grunting]
-[blade clinking]

78
00:05:02,333 --> 00:05:03,583
[groaning]

79
00:05:04,541 --> 00:05:06,416
[DONNA]
I only have one target,

80
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:08,875
but if you get in my way...

81
00:05:08,958 --> 00:05:11,125
-[panting]
-[DERRIDA] Come on, this way!

82
00:05:12,083 --> 00:05:13,375
-Get in!
-[grunt]

83
00:05:13,458 --> 00:05:15,416
I don't know who you
people are, but I'm not--

84
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:17,750
Hey, Graham! Please save Vidaux!

85
00:05:17,833 --> 00:05:20,666
[GRAHAM] Negative. I have been
ordered to protect Mayuka.

86
00:05:20,750 --> 00:05:21,958
Papa!

87
00:05:22,041 --> 00:05:23,833
I told you to stay inside!

88
00:05:23,916 --> 00:05:25,291
Oh no! You're bleeding!

89
00:05:25,375 --> 00:05:26,833
[VIDAUX]
It's okay, sweetheart.

90
00:05:26,916 --> 00:05:29,291
Who the hell did you piss off
to get her on your tail?

91
00:05:29,375 --> 00:05:31,625
-What?
-That's Donna, the White Death.

92
00:05:31,708 --> 00:05:33,083
An assassin who'll
chase her prey

93
00:05:33,166 --> 00:05:34,791
all the way to
the depths of Hell.

94
00:05:34,875 --> 00:05:36,916
-Way past being just a Destruct.
-[pressing buttons]

95
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,958
She's the most terrifying
killer out there.

96
00:05:39,041 --> 00:05:40,791
And she's coming after me?

97
00:05:40,875 --> 00:05:42,125
[VIDAUX]
And I wanna know why!

98
00:05:42,208 --> 00:05:43,208
[gasp]

99
00:05:43,291 --> 00:05:44,208
People don't hire
someone like her

100
00:05:44,291 --> 00:05:45,958
unless it's pretty damn serious.

101
00:05:46,041 --> 00:05:47,875
This is gonna cost you extra!

102
00:05:47,958 --> 00:05:50,000
-[engine roaring]
-[wind blowing]

103
00:05:51,333 --> 00:05:52,875
[GRAHAM]
Target locked from behind.

104
00:05:54,541 --> 00:05:55,541
[cocks gun]

105
00:05:55,625 --> 00:05:57,000
Let's shake her off!

106
00:05:57,083 --> 00:05:58,000
[blast]

107
00:05:58,083 --> 00:05:59,208
-[tires screech]
-[explosion]

108
00:05:59,291 --> 00:06:01,875
[screeching]

109
00:06:08,666 --> 00:06:10,416
♪

110
00:06:11,958 --> 00:06:13,541
-[phone ringing]
-Huh?

111
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:17,125
Excuse me for just a moment.

112
00:06:17,208 --> 00:06:18,500
[chuckling]

113
00:06:19,500 --> 00:06:20,708
[cough]

114
00:06:20,791 --> 00:06:22,000
It's me. What is it?

115
00:06:22,083 --> 00:06:23,708
[DONNA]
I'm changing the plan.

116
00:06:23,791 --> 00:06:26,791
Huh? What are you going to do?
I don't want you drawing atten--

117
00:06:26,875 --> 00:06:29,000
[DONNA] The state of battle
is in constant flux.

118
00:06:29,083 --> 00:06:30,708
-[hangs up]
-Hold on, wait a second!

119
00:06:30,791 --> 00:06:32,666
Did you hang up? Hello?!

120
00:06:32,750 --> 00:06:34,291
[clicking]

121
00:06:35,666 --> 00:06:36,625
[uncocks gun]

122
00:06:37,833 --> 00:06:39,708
[YURI] Hey, where do you
think you're going?

123
00:06:39,791 --> 00:06:41,750
I'm not a part of this,
you hear me?

124
00:06:41,833 --> 00:06:43,541
[VIDAUX] Then you can
go ahead and jump out.

125
00:06:43,625 --> 00:06:46,333
Um... Do you think you could
maybe pull over first?

126
00:06:46,416 --> 00:06:49,458
I won't stop until I'm sure
we're in a safe place.

127
00:06:49,541 --> 00:06:51,291
That's one of my
regulations, kid.

128
00:06:51,375 --> 00:06:52,708
[sigh]

129
00:06:52,791 --> 00:06:54,458
But, we're not even
being followed anymore.

130
00:06:54,541 --> 00:06:57,500
[VIDAUX] You really believe
that she'll give up that easily?

131
00:06:57,583 --> 00:06:59,125
[sigh]

132
00:07:00,458 --> 00:07:01,791
This is all your fault.

133
00:07:01,875 --> 00:07:04,166
You're the reason
I'm wrapped up in this.

134
00:07:05,125 --> 00:07:07,000
It isn't exactly
pleasant for me, either.

135
00:07:07,083 --> 00:07:10,166
It's like some kind
of twisted nightmare.

136
00:07:10,250 --> 00:07:12,958
Mage's dead, and I'm being
hunted down by a killer?

137
00:07:14,041 --> 00:07:17,083
What the hell is wrong
with this godforsaken place?!

138
00:07:17,166 --> 00:07:18,791
[MAYUKA]
He told this weird story.

139
00:07:18,875 --> 00:07:21,166
about how he's been
asleep for 10 years!

140
00:07:21,250 --> 00:07:22,916
For 10 years?

141
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:24,458
-[beeping]
-[GRAHAM] Target locked!

142
00:07:24,541 --> 00:07:25,708
-Behind and above!
-[gasp]

143
00:07:25,791 --> 00:07:28,541
-[jets whining]
-I knew she'd be back!

144
00:07:28,625 --> 00:07:31,583
He musta been someone really
important back then, huh?

145
00:07:31,666 --> 00:07:33,958
Yeah, well, he doesn't look all
that special, if you ask me.

146
00:07:34,041 --> 00:07:35,458
♪

147
00:07:35,541 --> 00:07:37,750
[VIDAUX] Hey, how much
more can I put on your tab?

148
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:40,208
Protecting you from
her won't come cheap.

149
00:07:40,291 --> 00:07:42,583
Whatever, I don't care!
Charge as much as you want!

150
00:07:42,666 --> 00:07:44,083
Hmm...

151
00:07:44,166 --> 00:07:46,500
Sounds like something a guy
with no money would say.

152
00:07:46,583 --> 00:07:48,083
Alright everyone, hold tight!

153
00:07:48,166 --> 00:07:49,791
-[restraints clicking]
-Huh? What--

154
00:07:49,875 --> 00:07:52,416
[roaring]

155
00:07:52,500 --> 00:07:55,041
[gunfire]

156
00:07:55,125 --> 00:07:56,583
-[tires screeching]
-[screaming]

157
00:07:56,666 --> 00:07:58,500
[VIDAUX] Mouth shut!
You'll bite your tongue off!

158
00:07:58,583 --> 00:08:00,958
Hey Graham,
any base camps nearby?

159
00:08:01,041 --> 00:08:02,250
[GRAHAM]
Camp Exon is approximately

160
00:08:02,333 --> 00:08:03,416
-four kilometers ahead.
-[beeping]

161
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:04,500
Got it.

162
00:08:04,583 --> 00:08:07,375
-[gunfire]
-[tires screeching]

163
00:08:08,875 --> 00:08:10,041
[jets whining]

164
00:08:10,125 --> 00:08:11,208
You won't escape.

165
00:08:11,291 --> 00:08:12,541
[beeping]

166
00:08:12,625 --> 00:08:14,666
-[gunfire]
-[tires screeching]

167
00:08:17,958 --> 00:08:19,375
[engine roaring]

168
00:08:19,458 --> 00:08:20,750
[groaning]

169
00:08:24,416 --> 00:08:27,000
[gunfire]

170
00:08:28,375 --> 00:08:29,708
[explosions]

171
00:08:29,791 --> 00:08:31,208
[tires screeching]

172
00:08:35,708 --> 00:08:37,541
[GRAHAM]
800 meters to base camp.

173
00:08:37,625 --> 00:08:38,625
It's about to get bumpy.

174
00:08:38,708 --> 00:08:41,666
♪

175
00:08:44,250 --> 00:08:45,541
We're almost there.

176
00:08:46,875 --> 00:08:48,708
[tires screeching]

177
00:08:48,791 --> 00:08:50,000
-[thud]
-[roaring]

178
00:08:52,166 --> 00:08:53,208
[smash]

179
00:08:55,541 --> 00:08:57,375
Do you really think
it'll be that easy?

180
00:08:57,458 --> 00:08:59,125
[machinery whirring]

181
00:08:59,208 --> 00:09:01,000
[launching]

182
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:04,125
[explosions]

183
00:09:04,208 --> 00:09:05,708
[YURI]
The way out!

184
00:09:05,791 --> 00:09:07,833
[rocks tumbling]

185
00:09:09,791 --> 00:09:11,333
[jets whining]

186
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:22,833
[ANDREI gasping]

187
00:09:22,916 --> 00:09:24,375
[LILY]
Spill imminent.

188
00:09:24,458 --> 00:09:26,250
Warning. Milk tea will spill.

189
00:09:26,333 --> 00:09:27,375
-[splash]
-Milk tea has spilled.

190
00:09:27,458 --> 00:09:29,041
[ANDREI]
That woman!

191
00:09:29,125 --> 00:09:30,916
What the hell does
she think she's doing?

192
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:33,166
-Is she out of her mind?!
-[splat]

193
00:09:33,250 --> 00:09:35,458
Oh... my shortcake!

194
00:09:35,541 --> 00:09:38,083
[car whirring, clattering]

195
00:09:44,541 --> 00:09:45,833
[click, buzz]

196
00:09:45,916 --> 00:09:47,916
[VIDAUX]
Okay, everyone out.

197
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,750
[YURI sighs]
Finally.

198
00:09:49,833 --> 00:09:51,125
[MAYUKA]
Whoa...

199
00:09:52,166 --> 00:09:53,708
[YURI sighs]

200
00:09:56,625 --> 00:09:57,750
Where are we?

201
00:09:57,833 --> 00:09:59,791
[VIDAUX]
A supply base for emergencies.

202
00:09:59,875 --> 00:10:01,958
I have a few others
hidden here and there.

203
00:10:02,041 --> 00:10:03,375
♪

204
00:10:03,458 --> 00:10:05,208
-[click]
-Can I take pictures in here?

205
00:10:05,291 --> 00:10:06,833
[VIDAUX]
Knock yourself out.

206
00:10:08,208 --> 00:10:09,916
Hey, will you take my picture?

207
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,833
[sigh]
Sure.

208
00:10:11,916 --> 00:10:13,750
-Mmm!
-[shutter clicks]

209
00:10:14,708 --> 00:10:15,791
[sigh]

210
00:10:15,875 --> 00:10:18,583
Damn it. She really got us good.

211
00:10:26,583 --> 00:10:27,458
[shutter click]

212
00:10:31,500 --> 00:10:33,708
You ambushed me
like that before.

213
00:10:33,791 --> 00:10:35,500
You haven't changed.

214
00:10:35,583 --> 00:10:37,000
When did I do that?

215
00:10:37,083 --> 00:10:38,875
Mage's birthday party.

216
00:10:38,958 --> 00:10:40,250
When she turned 8 years old.

217
00:10:40,333 --> 00:10:43,458
But, that was so many
years ago. Are you sure?

218
00:10:44,416 --> 00:10:47,500
To me, it's like it
was just yesterday.

219
00:10:49,958 --> 00:10:52,583
[VIDAUX] Hey, Derrida.
Come here for a minute.

220
00:10:52,666 --> 00:10:54,000
Sure.

221
00:10:56,750 --> 00:10:58,666
-[sigh]
-[clicking]

222
00:10:58,750 --> 00:11:00,791
[YURI]
10 years ago.

223
00:11:00,875 --> 00:11:03,000
At Mage's birthday party?

224
00:11:03,083 --> 00:11:06,125
♪

225
00:11:08,208 --> 00:11:11,041
Oh, come on.
There's just no way.

226
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:13,083
[sigh]

227
00:11:14,916 --> 00:11:16,000
[camera clicks]

228
00:11:16,083 --> 00:11:18,041
Are you really him?

229
00:11:18,125 --> 00:11:19,500
You're Derrida?

230
00:11:19,583 --> 00:11:21,000
-[wrench cranking]
-Is there a way

231
00:11:21,083 --> 00:11:23,333
-for us to get out?
-[VIDAUX] Yeah, a back entrance.

232
00:11:23,416 --> 00:11:24,458
[sigh]

233
00:11:25,416 --> 00:11:26,958
Hand me that ratchet, will you?

234
00:11:31,250 --> 00:11:33,666
So? [clears throat]
What happens now?

235
00:11:33,750 --> 00:11:35,083
What do you mean?

236
00:11:35,166 --> 00:11:36,375
[VIDAUX] I don't mind
being your bodyguard,

237
00:11:36,458 --> 00:11:38,625
if you can pay me eventually.

238
00:11:38,708 --> 00:11:41,416
But, if that girl's
gonna keep following you,

239
00:11:41,500 --> 00:11:43,416
I'm gonna need to charge extra.

240
00:11:45,833 --> 00:11:47,625
Number four wrench.

241
00:11:47,708 --> 00:11:49,208
[rummages]

242
00:11:49,291 --> 00:11:52,000
Listen, I'll pay you.

243
00:11:52,083 --> 00:11:54,708
Please just take
Yuri home for me.

244
00:11:54,791 --> 00:11:58,250
Are you really that valuable,
do you think?

245
00:11:58,333 --> 00:11:59,750
[cranking]

246
00:11:59,833 --> 00:12:01,166
Probably.

247
00:12:01,250 --> 00:12:02,791
[VIDAUX]
And what if you're not?

248
00:12:04,666 --> 00:12:06,625
-Number two.
-[rummages]

249
00:12:06,708 --> 00:12:08,125
Then, I guess...

250
00:12:09,083 --> 00:12:10,541
I'll be your servant for life.

251
00:12:10,625 --> 00:12:12,500
Not that one! I said number two!

252
00:12:12,583 --> 00:12:14,875
Right.

253
00:12:19,458 --> 00:12:20,500
Sorry.

254
00:12:22,916 --> 00:12:24,458
[wrench cranking]

255
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:29,041
[WOMAN, overlapping]
Clockwise. Anti-clockwise.

256
00:12:33,041 --> 00:12:34,791
[YURI]
There's a city up ahead.

257
00:12:34,875 --> 00:12:37,416
You can stock up on
food at the market.

258
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:39,375
[VIDAUX]
Sounds good.

259
00:12:39,458 --> 00:12:40,500
[car approaching]

260
00:12:43,833 --> 00:12:45,208
[YURI]
Alright.

261
00:12:46,166 --> 00:12:48,208
-[MAYUKA gasps]
-Is this close enough?

262
00:12:48,291 --> 00:12:49,916
Yeah, this'll work great!

263
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:51,500
What a big city!

264
00:12:51,583 --> 00:12:52,833
[DERRIDA] It looks like the war

265
00:12:52,916 --> 00:12:54,166
-has reached here too.
-[VIDAUX] Which way

266
00:12:54,250 --> 00:12:56,916
-is the market?
-Follow me, I'll show you.

267
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:59,916
[crowd chatter]

268
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:03,041
♪

269
00:13:11,625 --> 00:13:12,958
[VIDAUX]
Hmm...

270
00:13:14,416 --> 00:13:15,875
-[smack]
-[MAYUKA groans]

271
00:13:15,958 --> 00:13:17,333
[WOMAN]
Oh, Yuri!

272
00:13:17,416 --> 00:13:19,083
It's been so long!

273
00:13:19,166 --> 00:13:21,000
Dear, come here, it's Yuri!

274
00:13:21,083 --> 00:13:23,166
Oh! How 'bout that, doing well?

275
00:13:23,250 --> 00:13:25,458
Did you happen to find
what you were looking for?

276
00:13:25,541 --> 00:13:26,791
Huh?

277
00:13:26,875 --> 00:13:29,500
Oh, uh, no, not yet!

278
00:13:29,583 --> 00:13:32,333
[WOMAN] That's too bad.
I hope you find it soon!

279
00:13:32,416 --> 00:13:33,500
Yeah! Thank you!

280
00:13:36,500 --> 00:13:38,458
Hey. What's with this place?

281
00:13:38,541 --> 00:13:39,875
Uh...

282
00:13:41,041 --> 00:13:41,958
[sigh]

283
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:45,333
[YURI] It was built
after the war started.

284
00:13:45,416 --> 00:13:47,416
Most of the residents
made their way here

285
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:49,416
as refugees from all over,

286
00:13:49,500 --> 00:13:51,541
after being driven
from their homes.

287
00:13:55,458 --> 00:13:57,041
I see.

288
00:13:58,958 --> 00:14:00,250
-[VIDAUX] You two.
-[BOTH] Hmm?

289
00:14:00,333 --> 00:14:02,083
What are you staring at?

290
00:14:02,166 --> 00:14:03,958
Let's get going,
we're done here.

291
00:14:04,041 --> 00:14:05,500
[DERRIDA]
Got it.

292
00:14:06,791 --> 00:14:07,750
[sigh]

293
00:14:07,833 --> 00:14:09,583
♪

294
00:14:09,666 --> 00:14:12,708
-[MAYUKA] What a haul!
-[VIDAUX sighs]

295
00:14:12,791 --> 00:14:15,583
Glad they had a lot of
good stuff for sale.

296
00:14:15,666 --> 00:14:16,750
Yuri.

297
00:14:16,833 --> 00:14:19,416
I'm sorry I dragged
you into this.

298
00:14:19,500 --> 00:14:20,791
Guess it's time
for goodbyes.

299
00:14:20,875 --> 00:14:22,208
Thanks.

300
00:14:23,708 --> 00:14:24,750
[sigh]

301
00:14:26,708 --> 00:14:28,375
-No, wait!
-Huh?

302
00:14:29,333 --> 00:14:31,791
[birds chirping]

303
00:14:37,458 --> 00:14:40,166
[footsteps]

304
00:14:43,125 --> 00:14:44,375
You and Mage.

305
00:14:44,458 --> 00:14:46,000
This is where both of you lived?

306
00:14:46,083 --> 00:14:47,625
Yeah.

307
00:14:57,750 --> 00:14:59,291
[twists knob, door creaks]

308
00:15:01,916 --> 00:15:03,625
[flips switch, lights buzz]

309
00:15:09,541 --> 00:15:11,416
-Mrs. Hudson?
-Um...

310
00:15:13,291 --> 00:15:14,708
What's she doing here?

311
00:15:14,791 --> 00:15:16,708
[YURI] She's been
with us the whole time.

312
00:15:16,791 --> 00:15:18,750
Taking care of me and Mage.

313
00:15:19,708 --> 00:15:20,958
How's her battery?

314
00:15:21,041 --> 00:15:23,041
Well, I put her in
sleep mode a while ago.

315
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:26,833
She was a precious friend
to us when we were little,

316
00:15:26,916 --> 00:15:29,083
and I suppose
she still is, to me.

317
00:15:30,041 --> 00:15:32,791
I see. You've had her.

318
00:15:32,875 --> 00:15:34,041
-Um...
-Huh?

319
00:15:34,125 --> 00:15:35,458
Here.

320
00:15:35,541 --> 00:15:36,583
Pictures.

321
00:15:42,875 --> 00:15:44,291
Is that Mage?

322
00:15:44,375 --> 00:15:46,458
-I have some here, too!
-Oh.

323
00:15:46,541 --> 00:15:47,791
How do you use that again?

324
00:15:47,875 --> 00:15:50,291
You go like this, here. See?

325
00:15:50,375 --> 00:15:53,083
♪

326
00:15:59,458 --> 00:16:02,041
Oh yeah, and then
after this happened,

327
00:16:02,125 --> 00:16:04,375
Nathan told me he left
Mage at your house.

328
00:16:04,458 --> 00:16:07,333
Yeah. At first, the two of
us stayed with my family.

329
00:16:07,416 --> 00:16:09,708
But then, the war got worse,

330
00:16:09,791 --> 00:16:12,791
and they decided that it
would be best to go abroad.

331
00:16:12,875 --> 00:16:15,958
However, Mage and I didn't
want to leave the country.

332
00:16:16,916 --> 00:16:19,125
We convinced my parents
to let us stay,

333
00:16:19,208 --> 00:16:20,250
and we lived here.

334
00:16:20,333 --> 00:16:22,250
Every so often,

335
00:16:22,333 --> 00:16:23,458
people from Rebuild,

336
00:16:23,541 --> 00:16:25,125
or the police,
would come by to see us.

337
00:16:25,208 --> 00:16:26,458
[gasp]

338
00:16:26,541 --> 00:16:28,750
They kept asking,
"Has Derrida been here?".

339
00:16:28,833 --> 00:16:30,458
Pretty weird, isn't it?

340
00:16:30,541 --> 00:16:33,208
If you believed the news,
that was a dead man.

341
00:16:33,291 --> 00:16:34,541
[sigh]

342
00:16:34,625 --> 00:16:36,750
But Mage was convinced
the media was wrong.

343
00:16:36,833 --> 00:16:38,875
That Derrida was still alive.

344
00:16:38,958 --> 00:16:41,416
That he'd come here
for us one day.

345
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:42,375
[sigh]

346
00:16:43,333 --> 00:16:45,916
[DERRIDA] Mage believed in me,
even after what happened?

347
00:16:46,875 --> 00:16:48,333
But, I was too late!

348
00:16:49,291 --> 00:16:50,250
[sob]

349
00:16:50,333 --> 00:16:51,916
I didn't make it in time.

350
00:16:53,750 --> 00:16:54,750
Uh...

351
00:16:55,875 --> 00:16:56,916
[sigh]

352
00:16:58,333 --> 00:16:59,500
Well I, uh...

353
00:16:59,583 --> 00:17:01,458
I haven't been...

354
00:17:01,541 --> 00:17:03,583
-truthful.
-Huh?

355
00:17:05,333 --> 00:17:06,500
She's actually...

356
00:17:06,583 --> 00:17:08,416
-alive.
-[gasp]

357
00:17:08,500 --> 00:17:11,375
♪

358
00:17:11,458 --> 00:17:12,333
Hmm?

359
00:17:13,583 --> 00:17:14,708
[VIDAUX]
What the...

360
00:17:15,666 --> 00:17:17,666
What are you talking about?

361
00:17:17,750 --> 00:17:19,083
You said...

362
00:17:19,166 --> 00:17:21,375
you said she had died!

363
00:17:21,458 --> 00:17:22,666
She had a grave!

364
00:17:22,750 --> 00:17:24,125
That's...

365
00:17:24,208 --> 00:17:26,416
-a fake that I made.
-Huh?

366
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:28,375
I knew that someone
was after Mage,

367
00:17:28,458 --> 00:17:30,833
and I had to do
something to protect her.

368
00:17:30,916 --> 00:17:32,666
So, I pretended
that she was dead,

369
00:17:32,750 --> 00:17:34,875
and I put up
the grave as a decoy.

370
00:17:34,958 --> 00:17:36,375
Then where is she right now?

371
00:17:37,333 --> 00:17:39,041
That, I don't know.

372
00:17:39,125 --> 00:17:40,416
Without telling me,

373
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:42,791
she ran off somewhere last fall.

374
00:17:42,875 --> 00:17:44,666
I've been searching
for her, but...

375
00:17:44,750 --> 00:17:45,791
[sigh]

376
00:17:52,625 --> 00:17:54,333
All of this is my fault.

377
00:17:54,416 --> 00:17:55,625
I gave her that thing,

378
00:17:55,708 --> 00:17:58,041
and because of that,
she's in danger now.

379
00:17:59,125 --> 00:18:00,208
[growl]

380
00:18:00,291 --> 00:18:02,708
We need to go
and track her down!

381
00:18:02,791 --> 00:18:04,041
Derrida...

382
00:18:04,125 --> 00:18:05,791
I believe you,

383
00:18:05,875 --> 00:18:07,541
-and your story.
-Huh?

384
00:18:08,500 --> 00:18:09,666
When you were crying earlier,

385
00:18:09,750 --> 00:18:12,083
it didn't look like
crocodile tears.

386
00:18:12,166 --> 00:18:13,625
You were genuinely concerned!

387
00:18:14,916 --> 00:18:15,958
Yuri, I...

388
00:18:16,041 --> 00:18:18,000
And I also believe
you when you say

389
00:18:18,083 --> 00:18:20,208
that you came here
from 10 years ago.

390
00:18:20,291 --> 00:18:21,416
Crazy as it is.

391
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:23,541
Oh Yuri, thank you!

392
00:18:23,625 --> 00:18:24,875
If Mage is still alive,

393
00:18:24,958 --> 00:18:26,916
-I know we can find her!
-[birds cawing]

394
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:28,375
I'll go get Vidaux.

395
00:18:28,458 --> 00:18:29,708
[footsteps]

396
00:18:29,791 --> 00:18:31,708
[wind blowing]

397
00:18:33,333 --> 00:18:35,000
-[crackling]
-[gasp]

398
00:18:35,083 --> 00:18:37,166
Is this fog?
[gasp]

399
00:18:38,125 --> 00:18:39,333
♪

400
00:18:39,416 --> 00:18:41,500
-[clock ticking slower]
-[energy humming]

401
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:47,541
It's you again.

402
00:18:49,166 --> 00:18:52,375
[inaudible]

403
00:18:52,458 --> 00:18:54,708
Ange, right?
What are you trying to tell me?

404
00:18:54,791 --> 00:18:57,416
[clock ticking faster]

405
00:18:57,500 --> 00:18:58,708
[energy humming]

406
00:18:58,791 --> 00:19:00,708
Wait, was she...

407
00:19:00,791 --> 00:19:02,166
pointing at Yuri?

408
00:19:03,125 --> 00:19:04,333
[growl]

409
00:19:05,875 --> 00:19:08,208
-[click]
-[air rushing]

410
00:19:08,291 --> 00:19:09,791
[explosion]

411
00:19:09,875 --> 00:19:11,750
Yuri, no! I'm coming!

412
00:19:11,833 --> 00:19:13,166
[glass shattering]

413
00:19:13,250 --> 00:19:15,500
[YURI coughing, choking]

414
00:19:15,583 --> 00:19:17,625
[gasping, panting]

415
00:19:19,166 --> 00:19:20,833
Just hang on!

416
00:19:20,916 --> 00:19:21,875
[panting]

417
00:19:22,833 --> 00:19:25,083
[groaning]

418
00:19:26,541 --> 00:19:28,708
[screaming]

419
00:19:28,791 --> 00:19:30,250
[grunting]

420
00:19:30,333 --> 00:19:33,166
[debris falling]

421
00:19:33,250 --> 00:19:35,708
[whimpering]

422
00:19:35,791 --> 00:19:37,541
Yuri! You okay?

423
00:19:38,500 --> 00:19:40,875
[DERRIDA]
You're safe now. Can you stand?

424
00:19:40,958 --> 00:19:42,500
[YURI]
Yeah.

425
00:19:44,041 --> 00:19:44,833
[gasp]

426
00:19:44,916 --> 00:19:46,541
I need to save her!

427
00:19:46,625 --> 00:19:47,958
-Yuri, wait!
-Mrs. Hudson!

428
00:19:48,041 --> 00:19:49,291
And my pictures of Mage!

429
00:19:49,375 --> 00:19:51,125
-No!
-Let me go!

430
00:19:51,208 --> 00:19:52,583
You can't!

431
00:19:52,666 --> 00:19:54,250
-If you go in, you'll...
-[crying]

432
00:19:54,333 --> 00:19:56,333
[engine revving, tires screech]

433
00:19:57,458 --> 00:19:58,375
[VIDAUX]
Get in.

434
00:19:59,958 --> 00:20:01,500
[door closes, engine roars]

435
00:20:01,583 --> 00:20:02,750
[dust flying]

436
00:20:02,833 --> 00:20:04,250
Damn, I can't believe
they'd blow up

437
00:20:04,333 --> 00:20:05,833
the whole building
just to get to you.

438
00:20:05,916 --> 00:20:08,041
Do you think it was that woman
from the gravesite again?

439
00:20:08,125 --> 00:20:09,750
[VIDAUX]
No, probably someone else.

440
00:20:09,833 --> 00:20:11,666
I saw some shady
guys lurking around

441
00:20:11,750 --> 00:20:13,916
-just before the explosion.
-[DERRIDA sighs]

442
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:16,166
I've really got my hands
full with the two of you.

443
00:20:16,250 --> 00:20:18,833
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

444
00:20:18,916 --> 00:20:20,833
[crying]
Mage.

445
00:20:23,416 --> 00:20:25,250
[breeze blowing]

446
00:20:25,333 --> 00:20:27,208
-[ringing]
-[ANDREI] It's me.

447
00:20:27,291 --> 00:20:29,625
This wasn't part of
the plan we agreed on.

448
00:20:29,708 --> 00:20:31,041
Did you order this?

449
00:20:31,125 --> 00:20:33,416
[laughing]
Whatever do you mean?

450
00:20:33,500 --> 00:20:35,500
-Stop interfering, you fool.
-[gasp]

451
00:20:35,583 --> 00:20:39,500
If you're going to insist on
sending others after my target,

452
00:20:39,583 --> 00:20:41,750
be prepared for
collateral damage.

453
00:20:41,833 --> 00:20:42,916
-[hangs up]
-[gasp]

454
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:45,250
Hey! Hello?!

455
00:20:46,208 --> 00:20:48,083
She hung up again!

456
00:20:48,166 --> 00:20:50,250
[grunt] Hang up on me,
I'll hang you up!

457
00:20:50,333 --> 00:20:52,916
How dare you do this to me,
I deserve better!

458
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:54,958
♪

459
00:20:55,041 --> 00:20:56,541
[VIDAUX]
We've been through a lot today.

460
00:20:56,625 --> 00:20:58,625
I think we've earned some rest.

461
00:20:58,708 --> 00:21:00,375
Yeah, I'm tired!

462
00:21:00,458 --> 00:21:02,000
[opens trunk]

463
00:21:03,208 --> 00:21:04,416
Yuri...

464
00:21:06,083 --> 00:21:07,375
I'm sorry.

465
00:21:07,458 --> 00:21:09,708
If only we hadn't gone
to your house, then...

466
00:21:09,791 --> 00:21:11,208
Tomorrow, I'll talk to Vidaux,

467
00:21:11,291 --> 00:21:13,458
and have him take you to
go find your parents, okay?

468
00:21:14,416 --> 00:21:16,291
I'll look for Mage myself.

469
00:21:17,250 --> 00:21:18,916
And if I find her,

470
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:20,750
I promise that
I'll let you know.

471
00:21:20,833 --> 00:21:22,041
Count on it.

472
00:21:22,125 --> 00:21:23,625
-No, I won't.
-Huh?

473
00:21:23,708 --> 00:21:24,666
[grunt]

474
00:21:24,750 --> 00:21:25,875
'Cause I'm going, too,

475
00:21:25,958 --> 00:21:27,708
-to help search for Mage!
-Huh?

476
00:21:27,791 --> 00:21:28,958
Besides,

477
00:21:29,041 --> 00:21:30,208
not like I have
anywhere to go,

478
00:21:30,291 --> 00:21:31,916
thanks to you mixing
me up in all this!

479
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:34,000
But you know we could get
attacked again at any time!

480
00:21:34,083 --> 00:21:35,166
Well, I don't care!

481
00:21:35,250 --> 00:21:36,833
I'll face any danger head-on

482
00:21:36,916 --> 00:21:38,791
if it means that I get
to see Mage again!

483
00:21:38,875 --> 00:21:41,416
And that's final.
I've made up my mind!

484
00:21:42,375 --> 00:21:43,833
I'll be joining the team!

485
00:21:43,916 --> 00:21:46,208
-Huh?
-Are you really, Yuri?

486
00:21:46,291 --> 00:21:48,166
And who exactly's
paying your way?

487
00:21:48,250 --> 00:21:50,250
-Oh, you know.
-Uh...

488
00:21:50,333 --> 00:21:51,750
I get it!

489
00:21:51,833 --> 00:21:53,125
Really, now.

490
00:21:53,208 --> 00:21:56,000
[MAYUKA] Yay!
I get to stay with Big Sis!

491
00:21:56,083 --> 00:21:58,375
[VIDAUX] I'll expect full
compensation for this.

492
00:21:58,458 --> 00:22:00,166
-Keep that in mind.
-[grunt]

493
00:22:00,250 --> 00:22:02,541
Sure! You can just
put it all on my tab!

494
00:22:02,625 --> 00:22:04,166
[giggle]

